The molar internal energy change for an isothermal process is obtained from the internal pressure  

\[
\pi_T=\left(\frac{\partial U}{\partial V}\right)_T=\frac{a}{V_m^{2}}
\]

Hence  

\[
\Delta U_m=\int_{V_{1}}^{V_{2}}\frac{a}{V_m^{2}}\,dV_m
          =-a\left[\frac{1}{V_m}\right]_{V_{1}}^{V_{2}}
          =a\left(\frac{1}{V_{1}}-\frac{1}{V_{2}}\right)
\]

For nitrogen (van‑der‑Waals constant)  

\[
a = 1.390\;\text{L}^{2}\,\text{bar mol}^{-2}
   =1.390\times10^{-1}\;\text{Pa·m}^{6}\,\text{mol}^{-2}
   =0.139\;\text{J·m}^{3}\,\text{mol}^{-2}
\]

Convert the volumes to cubic metres (per mole):

\[
V_{1}=1.00\;\text{dm}^{3}=1.00\times10^{-3}\;\text{m}^{3},\qquad
V_{2}=24.8\;\text{dm}^{3}=2.48\times10^{-2}\;\text{m}^{3}
