The equilibrium for the formation of silver(I) oxide is  

\[
2\,\text{Ag(s)}+\tfrac12\,\text{O}_2(g)\;\rightleftharpoons\;\text{Ag}_2\text{O(s)}
\]

For this reaction the equilibrium constant (activities of solids are 1) is  

\[
K=\frac{a_{\text{Ag}_2\text{O}}}{a_{\text{Ag}}^{\,2}\, (P_{\text{O}_2})^{1/2}}
      =\frac{1}{(P_{\text{O}_2})^{1/2}}
\]

At equilibrium \(\Delta G=0\), so  

\[
\Delta G^{\circ}= -RT\ln K
                = -RT\ln\!\left[\frac{1}{(P_{\text{O}_2})^{1/2}}\right]
                = \frac{RT}{2}\ln P_{\text{O}_2}
\]

The given equilibrium pressure is \(P_{\text{O}_2}=11.85\;\text{Pa}\).
Convert to the standard state of 1 bar:

\[
