The change in internal energy for an ideal gas is  

\[
\Delta U = nC_{V,m}(T_f-T_i)
\]

where the final temperature \(T_f\) is obtained from the adiabatic condition  
\(\Delta U = -w = -P_{\text{ext}}\Delta V\) with \(\Delta V = V_f-V_i\) and the ideal‑gas relation \(V=nRT/P\).

\[
\begin{aligned}
nC_{V,m}(T_f-T_i) &= -P_{\text{ext}}\!\left(\frac{nRT_f}{P_f}-\frac{nRT_i}{P_i}\right)\\[4pt]
\Rightarrow\; T_f &= T_i\;
\frac{C_{V,m}+ \dfrac{R P_{\text{ext}}}{P_i}}
     {C_{V,m}+ \dfrac{R P_{\text{ext}}}{P_f}} .
\end{aligned}
\]

Insert the data (\(n=2.50\;\text{mol},\; C_{V,m}=12.47\;\text{J mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1},\;
R=8.314\;\text{J mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1},\;
P_{\text{ext}}=1.00\;\text{bar},\;
P_i=2.50\;\text{bar},\;
P_f=1.25\;\text{bar},\;
T_i=325\;\text{K}\)):

\[
\begin{aligned}
\frac{R P_{\text{ext}}}{P_i} &= \frac{8.314\times1.00}{2.50}=3.33\;\text{J mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1},\\
\frac{R P_{\text{ext}}}{P_f} &= \frac{8.314\times1.00}{1.25}=6.65\;\text{J mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1},\\[4pt]
T_f &= 325\;\text{K}\;
\frac{12.47+3.33}{12.47+6.65}
      = 325\;\text{K}\times0.826 \approx 2.69\times10^{2}\;\text{K}.
\end{aligned}
\]

Thus  

