\]

Hence the centre field for the X‑band frequency \(\nu = 9.5\;\text{GHz}\) is  

\[
B_{0}= \frac{h\nu}{g\mu_{\mathrm B}}
      =\frac{6.62607\times10^{-34}\,\text{J·s}\;(9.5\times10^{9}\,\text{s}^{-1})}
            {2.005\;(9.27401\times10^{-24}\,\text{J·T}^{-1})}
      \approx 0.3386\;\text{T}=338.6\;\text{mT}.
\]

The hyper‑fine splitting of the two lines is \(\Delta\nu = 280\;\text{MHz}\).  
The corresponding field separation is  

\[
\Delta B = \frac{h\Delta\nu}{g\mu_{\mathrm B}}
         =\frac{6.62607\times10^{-34}\,(2.80\times10^{8})}
                {2.005\;(9.27401\times10^{-24})}
         \approx 0.00999\;\text{T}=9.99\;\text{mT}.
\]

The two lines are symmetrically placed about \(B_{0}\); therefore the lower‑field line is  

