The absorbances at the two wavelengths are described by Beer's law for a mixture:

\[
\begin{cases}
A_{510}= \varepsilon_{\text{Co},510}\,c_{\text{Co}}+\varepsilon_{\text{Ni},510}\,c_{\text{Ni}} =0.446\\[4pt]
A_{656}= \varepsilon_{\text{Co},656}\,c_{\text{Co}}+\varepsilon_{\text{Ni},656}\,c_{\text{Ni}} =0.326
\end{cases}
\]

Insert the given molar absorptivities ( L mol\(^{-1}\) cm\(^{-1}\) ) and solve for the concentrations (with \(b=1.00\) cm):

\[
\begin{aligned}
36\,400\,c_{\text{Co}}+5\,520\,c_{\text{Ni}} &=0.446\\
1\,240\,c_{\text{Co}}+17\,500\,c_{\text{Ni}} &=0.326
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
c_{\text{Ni}} = 1.795\times10^{-5}\;\text{mol L}^{-1},\qquad
c_{\text{Co}} = 9.6\times10^{-6}\;\text{mol L}^{-1}
\]

The measured solution (final volume = 50.0 mL) therefore contains

\[
n_{\text{Ni}} = c_{\text{Ni}}\times 0.050\;\text{L}=8.98\times10^{-7}\;\text{mol}
\]

This amount originated from the 25.0 mL aliquot, i.e. it represents half of the nickel present in the original 50 mL digest. Hence the total moles of Ni in the original digest are

\[
n_{\text{Ni,total}} = 2\,n_{\text{Ni}} = 1.795\times10^{-6}\;\text{mol}
\]

Mass of Ni:

\[
m_{\text{Ni}} = n_{\text{Ni,total}}\;M_{\text{Ni}}
               = 1.795\times10^{-6}\;\text{mol}\times58.69\;\text{g mol}^{-1}
               = 1.054\times10^{-4}\;\text{g}
\]

The original solid sample weighed \(0.425\;\text{g}\).  The concentration in parts per million is

\[
\text{Ni (ppm)} = \frac{m_{\text{Ni}}}{0.425\;\text{g}}\times10^{6}
                = 2.48\times10^{2}\;\text{ppm}
\]

\[
\boxed{2.48\times10^{2}}\,\text{Ni(ppm)}
\]

The titration measures the number of acidic end‑groups of the PLA chains.  
Each polymer chain possesses one acidic end‑group, therefore the moles of KOH that react equal the moles of polymer molecules present.

1. **Moles of KOH used**

\[
\begin{aligned}
C_{\text{KOH}} &= 0.0400\ \text{mol L}^{-1}\\
V_{\text{KOH}} &= 6.81\ \text{cm}^{3}=6.81\times10^{-3}\ \text{L}\\[4pt]
n_{\text{KOH}} &= C_{\text{KOH}}\;V_{\text{KOH}}
               = 0.0400\ \frac{\text{mol}}{\text{L}}\times 6.81\times10^{-3}\ \text{L}\\
               &= 2.724\times10^{-4}\ \text{mol}
\end{aligned}
\]

2. **Moles of polymer chains**

\[
n_{\text{PLA}} = n_{\text{KOH}} = 2.724\times10^{-4}\ \text{mol}
\]

3. **Average molar mass of the polymer**

\[
\begin{aligned}
m_{\text{PLA}} &= 0.1619\ \text{g}\\[4pt]
\overline{M} &= \frac{m_{\text{PLA}}}{n_{\text{PLA}}}
             = \frac{0.1619\ \text{g}}{2.724\times10^{-4}\ \text{mol}}\\
             &\approx 5.95\times10^{2}\ \text{g mol}^{-1}
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{5.95\times10^{2}\ \text{g mol}^{-1}}
\]
